
terraform init — Prepare the working directory for use with Terraform
terraform init -get-plugins=false — Initialize the working directory, do not download plugins

terraform get — Downloads and installs modules needed for the configuration
terraform get -update — installs the newer versions if available
terraform validate — Validates the configuration files
terraform plan — Plan will generate an execution plan
terraform plan -out=<path> — Save the plan file to a given path
terraform plan -destroy — Creates a plan to destroy all objects

terraform apply — Creates or updates infrastructure depending on the configuration files
terraform apply -auto-approve — Apply changes without having to interactively type ‘yes’ to the plan

terraform apply -var="domainpassword=password123" — Pass in a variable value.
terraform apply -var-file="varfile.tfvars" — Pass in variables contained in a file

terraform destroy — Destroys the infrastructure managed by Terraform

terraform workspace show — Show the name of the current workspace
terraform workspace list — List your workspaces
